WEBVTT

02:00.037 --> 02:01.080
Mr. Soprano?

02:02.540 --> 02:03.707
Yeah.

02:14.510 --> 02:15.886
Have a seat.

02:45.708 --> 02:49.211
My understanding from Dr. Cusamano,
your physician...

02:49.420 --> 02:51.088
...is that you collapsed.

02:51.463 --> 02:55.092
Possibly a panic attack?
You were unable to breathe?

02:55.259 --> 02:58.220
They said it was a panic attack.

02:58.846 --> 03:01.849
The blood and neurological
work came back negative.

03:03.726 --> 03:05.436
And they sent me here.

03:05.603 --> 03:07.730
You don't agree that
you had a panic attack?

03:11.233 --> 03:13.110
How are you feeling now?

03:13.277 --> 03:14.361
Good.

03:14.778 --> 03:17.239
Fine. Back at work.

03:19.074 --> 03:20.784
What line of work are you in?

03:20.993 --> 03:23.245
Waste management consultant.

03:30.169 --> 03:33.464
It's impossible for me to
talk to a psychiatrist.

03:34.298 --> 03:38.010
Any thoughts at all
on why you blacked out?

03:39.970 --> 03:42.806
I don't know. Stress, maybe.

03:44.600 --> 03:45.809
About what?

03:53.525 --> 03:54.944
<i>I don't know.</i>

03:55.986 --> 03:58.989
<i>The morning I got sick,
I'd been thinking.</i>

04:01.450 --> 04:04.161
<i>It's good to be in something
from the ground floor.</i>

04:04.411 --> 04:07.498
<i>And I came too late for that, I know.</i>

04:07.706 --> 04:11.794
<i>But lately, I'm getting the feeling
that I came in at the end.</i>

04:12.002 --> 04:13.420
<i>The best is over.</i>

04:13.671 --> 04:16.840
<i>Many Americans, I think,
feel that way.</i>

04:18.133 --> 04:19.551
<i>I think about my father.</i>

04:19.843 --> 04:22.221
<i>He never reached the heights like me.</i>

04:22.513 --> 04:24.348
<i>In a lot of ways he had it better.</i>

04:24.640 --> 04:28.936
<i>He had his people, they had
their standards, they had pride.</i>

04:29.144 --> 04:30.813
<i>Today, what do we got?</i>

04:35.484 --> 04:40.197
Did you have these feelings of loss
more acutely before you collapsed?

04:41.573 --> 04:43.075
I don't know.

05:00.384 --> 05:04.263
<i>A couple months before, these
two ducks landed in my pool.</i>

05:04.513 --> 05:08.559
<i>It was amazing. They're from Canada,
and it was mating season.</i>

05:09.560 --> 05:11.687
<i>They had some ducklings.</i>

05:16.233 --> 05:17.901
Come on, get some bread.

05:26.243 --> 05:28.996
<i>My daughter's friend was there
to drive her to school.</i>

05:29.496 --> 05:33.584
- Meadow, your father with those ducks.
- The yard smells like duck poo.

05:33.792 --> 05:36.795
You gotta have more than
just juice for breakfast.

05:37.087 --> 05:41.258
You need brain food for school.
Happy birthday, handsome.

05:41.759 --> 05:43.802
- Thirteen.
- He doesn't act it.

05:44.053 --> 05:47.765
The male and female duck made
a home in your pool and did it?

05:48.015 --> 05:50.517
Get out of here! You're so gross!

05:50.726 --> 05:53.103
You want some of
last night's <i>sfogliatelle?</i>

05:53.771 --> 05:56.148
- Get out of here with that fat.
- One bite.

05:56.398 --> 05:58.108
How do you stay skinny,
Mrs. Soprano?

06:01.320 --> 06:03.947
Him, with those ducks.

06:04.114 --> 06:08.118
If you don't like that ramp, I'll
build another. Maybe it's the wood.

06:17.795 --> 06:19.630
Look, they're trying to fly.

06:21.548 --> 06:24.176
<i>- National Geographic,</i> Dad.
- Yeah, super.

06:24.426 --> 06:27.137
- You showed us yesterday.
- This is great!

06:27.638 --> 06:31.809
Now my wife feels
this friend is a bad influence.

06:31.975 --> 06:35.145
It's so cool you're coming to Aspen
with my family at Christmas.

06:35.354 --> 06:39.858
Last year I saw Skeet Ulrich,
as close as from where you're sitting.

06:40.109 --> 06:41.985
Miss Meadow, we made a deal.

06:42.277 --> 06:46.824
Keep your grades up and your curfew
until Christmas, then you get to go.

06:47.074 --> 06:48.659
I know that.

06:48.951 --> 06:49.952
Good morning.

06:50.160 --> 06:52.371
- Hey, Mr. Soprano.
- We're late, Dad.

06:52.663 --> 06:54.873
- Happy birthday.
- Thanks, Dad.

07:01.630 --> 07:06.176
You're gonna be home tonight for
Anthony Jr.'s birthday party, right?

07:08.512 --> 07:10.347
Birdman, hello!

07:10.514 --> 07:13.225
Yeah, yeah.
I'll get home early from work.

07:13.725 --> 07:16.186
I'm not talking about work.

07:19.398 --> 07:21.859
This won't work.
I can't talk about my personal life.

07:22.192 --> 07:25.028
Finish telling me
about the day you collapsed.

07:28.740 --> 07:32.661
<i>I drove to work with my nephew.
He's learning the business.</i>

07:32.870 --> 07:35.372
<i>He's an example of what
I was talking about before.</i>

07:35.539 --> 07:39.918
Did you call Triborough Towers
about the hauling contract?

07:40.419 --> 07:43.881
I got home too late.
I didn't want to wake the man up.

07:45.340 --> 07:48.719
Did you get up early and call?
He's always in his office by 6.

07:49.011 --> 07:52.890
I was nauseous. My mother told me
I shouldn't even come in today.

07:53.265 --> 07:57.060
<i>Bear in mind, this is a kid who
just bought himself a $60,000 Lexus.</i>

08:03.901 --> 08:06.028
- There's that guy Mahaffey.
- Get out.

08:06.236 --> 08:08.739
Right there.
Next to the boo-boo in pink.

08:10.240 --> 08:11.408
Back up.

08:22.252 --> 08:26.924
My friend Mahaffey
pulling his taffy. Hello.

08:27.090 --> 08:28.800
<i>We saw this guy.</i>

08:29.384 --> 08:31.220
There was an outstanding loan.

08:31.428 --> 08:32.596
One second.

08:34.473 --> 08:37.100
I don't know
where this story is going.

08:38.227 --> 08:42.564
But there are a few ethical ground
rules we should get out of the way.

08:44.107 --> 08:46.276
What you tell me here...

08:46.568 --> 08:49.780
...falls under
doctor/patient confidentiality.

08:49.988 --> 08:51.615
Except if I was...

08:53.492 --> 08:56.912
If I was to hear, let's say,
a murder was to take place...

08:57.120 --> 08:59.122
Not that it would, but if.

08:59.623 --> 09:03.293
If a patient tells me a story
where someone's going to get hurt...

09:03.752 --> 09:06.463
...I'm supposed to go
to the authorities.

09:07.714 --> 09:08.966
Technically.

09:13.136 --> 09:15.305
You said you were in waste management.

09:16.098 --> 09:17.140
The environment.

09:17.349 --> 09:20.227
Dr. Cusamano, besides
being your family physician...

09:20.435 --> 09:22.980
...is also your next-door neighbor.

09:23.230 --> 09:24.648
See what I'm saying?

09:24.856 --> 09:28.235
I don't know what happened
with this fellow, I'm...

09:28.443 --> 09:30.279
I'm just saying.

09:32.155 --> 09:33.365
Nothing.

09:34.116 --> 09:35.659
We had coffee.

09:36.660 --> 09:37.744
Alex!

09:37.995 --> 09:39.329
Help!

09:45.711 --> 09:48.005
Security! Help!

09:48.255 --> 09:49.965
Oh, shit.

10:09.693 --> 10:10.694
Asshole!

10:15.198 --> 10:16.199
Tony!

10:16.825 --> 10:17.868
Wait up!

10:24.207 --> 10:25.917
Security!

10:51.109 --> 10:52.110
You all right?

10:52.319 --> 10:54.738
My leg is broken.
The bone's coming through.

10:55.030 --> 10:56.073
Let me see.

10:56.239 --> 10:59.826
I'll give you a fucking bone,
you prick! Where's my fucking money?

11:00.869 --> 11:02.245
So you had coffee.

11:02.746 --> 11:03.914
Right.

11:04.122 --> 11:06.833
You son of a bitch, motherfucker.

11:10.837 --> 11:15.592
- What are you doing? Get over here!
- That's $3000 here. $3000.

11:15.842 --> 11:16.885
Go ahead.

11:20.222 --> 11:21.640
Where's the fucking money?

11:21.932 --> 11:23.266
I'll get the money!

11:23.558 --> 11:24.768
I know you will.

11:25.060 --> 11:28.271
You should get a cork in your mouth
because you say I'm nothing...

11:28.563 --> 11:31.274
...compared to the people
who used to run things. Prick.

11:32.275 --> 11:33.276
I'm nothing.

11:39.616 --> 11:40.784
Shut up.

11:42.369 --> 11:45.122
What are you crying about? HMO.
You're covered.

11:45.789 --> 11:47.082
You prick.

11:48.959 --> 11:51.128
Degenerate fucking gambler.

11:51.878 --> 11:52.879
<i>Go on.</i>

11:53.088 --> 11:54.631
<i>Next, I had a meeting.</i>

11:54.881 --> 11:58.427
<i>I was called in to consult by
a garbage-hauling company I represent.</i>

11:58.760 --> 12:00.637
What's the story
with Triborough Towers?

12:01.304 --> 12:05.642
The manager wants the contract
with Dick, but this Kolar Sanitation...

12:05.934 --> 12:07.811
Another nationwide company.

12:07.978 --> 12:11.815
The Kolar brothers. Czechoslovakian
immigrants or some shit.

12:12.023 --> 12:15.026
These Polacks will haul
paper, plastic and aluminum...

12:15.277 --> 12:16.945
...for 7000 a month less than Dick.

12:17.529 --> 12:19.823
They pay us 40 times the monthly
for stealing a stop.

12:19.990 --> 12:21.616
That's the thing. They won't.

12:21.992 --> 12:26.329
Says if he can tell the commie bosses
in Czechoslovakia to fuck off...

12:26.538 --> 12:28.331
...he can fucking tell us.

12:29.040 --> 12:31.126
- I give up.
- Fucking garbage business.

12:31.334 --> 12:33.545
Yeah, I know. It's all changing.

12:33.837 --> 12:35.505
Let me see what I can do.

12:36.339 --> 12:38.341
Sure? You over your stomachache?

12:38.550 --> 12:40.510
- Oh, yeah.
- Good.

12:41.970 --> 12:43.430
What are you doing here?

12:43.680 --> 12:46.725
Gabriella sends me
down here for the <i>capocollo.</i>

12:46.975 --> 12:49.436
Hey, T, let me ask you something.

12:49.686 --> 12:52.981
Didn't you used to go to school
with Artie Bucco?

12:53.190 --> 12:56.067
A situation came up.
It involves my uncle.

12:56.860 --> 12:58.487
I can't go into details.

12:58.695 --> 12:59.696
That's fine.

12:59.946 --> 13:04.034
But I will say this. My uncle
adds to my general stress level.

13:04.701 --> 13:06.703
It's none of my business...

13:07.204 --> 13:09.831
...but down at the club,
the word is...

13:10.040 --> 13:13.043
...your Uncle Junior
is gonna whack Pussy Malanga.

13:16.087 --> 13:18.882
He's gonna do it
at Artie Bucco's restaurant.

13:29.267 --> 13:31.520
Hey, boys. How are you?

13:34.064 --> 13:35.065
Don't move.

13:35.273 --> 13:37.734
- Uncle Junior, how you doing?
- Hey.

13:38.360 --> 13:39.986
Hey, good to see you.

13:40.237 --> 13:41.738
Hi there, Chris.

13:42.030 --> 13:46.076
I was talking about you. It's Anthony
Jr.'s birthday tonight, right?

13:46.284 --> 13:50.914
Don't buy him anything big,
we overindulge him. Okay?

13:52.415 --> 13:53.583
Hey!

13:54.251 --> 13:56.545
- Artie, how's your rash?
- It's itchy.

13:56.753 --> 13:57.796
Come here.

13:58.797 --> 14:02.050
- Good to see you. You'll come over?
- Yeah, have a seat.

14:06.221 --> 14:09.140
You know what it means, one of
these mutts gets wet in here?

14:10.100 --> 14:11.601
It'll ruin his business.

14:11.768 --> 14:14.062
You better sit down with your uncle.

14:17.440 --> 14:19.651
<i>Uncle Junior's my father's brother.</i>

14:19.943 --> 14:22.737
<i>A good guy, just getting old, cranky.</i>

14:24.614 --> 14:27.617
<i>He used to take me to Yankee games
when I was a kid.</i>

14:28.285 --> 14:29.619
<i>I love my uncle.</i>

14:31.162 --> 14:33.623
<i>At the same time, when I was young...</i>

14:33.790 --> 14:37.627
<i>...he told my girl cousins
I would never be a varsity athlete.</i>

14:37.794 --> 14:40.755
<i>Frankly, that was a tremendous blow
to my self-esteem.</i>

15:04.321 --> 15:05.363
Who's there?

15:05.655 --> 15:06.823
It's me, Ma.

15:08.116 --> 15:09.492
Who are you?

15:10.577 --> 15:11.995
Ma, open the door.

15:15.832 --> 15:19.127
- Anthony?
- Yeah, it's me. Open the door.

15:23.882 --> 15:25.592
Hi, how are you?

15:27.677 --> 15:29.679
Jeez, Ma. Get some air in here.

15:30.597 --> 15:32.390
Did you lock the door?

15:32.641 --> 15:36.019
- Yeah, I did.
- Somebody called here last night.

15:36.227 --> 15:38.396
- After dark.
- Who?

15:38.688 --> 15:41.232
You think I'd answer?
It was dark out.

15:41.524 --> 15:43.360
Ma, I'll never understand that.

15:43.526 --> 15:45.862
The phone is auditory.
Dark is an eye thing.

15:46.112 --> 15:49.491
I could understand not going out.
You could get jumped.

15:49.699 --> 15:50.867
But the phone?

15:51.117 --> 15:55.830
Listen to him, he knows everything.
You want some lunch? I got eggplant.

15:56.039 --> 15:59.376
No, no, I just ate.
Know who I just ran into?

15:59.542 --> 16:00.543
Uncle Jun.

16:00.752 --> 16:05.632
Oh, that one. You think he ever
comes to see his sister-in-law?

16:06.549 --> 16:08.134
Remember Artie Bucco?

16:08.385 --> 16:10.387
Kid I went to elementary school with?

16:10.637 --> 16:14.182
Oh, yeah, I still see his mother.

16:15.517 --> 16:17.435
She tells me...

16:17.686 --> 16:21.022
...he calls her every day.

16:21.231 --> 16:24.567
Well, Uncle Junior's gonna
make a problem for Artie.

16:24.859 --> 16:26.194
Could affect his livelihood.

16:26.403 --> 16:29.197
- What's that?
- CD player.

16:29.906 --> 16:31.282
For who?

16:31.574 --> 16:32.742
For me?

16:32.951 --> 16:35.036
- I don't want it.
- You don't want it.

16:35.245 --> 16:39.249
You love music, all the old stuff's
on CD. Your favorites.

16:39.457 --> 16:41.584
"Pajama Game," Connie Francis.

16:41.876 --> 16:42.919
Here.

16:46.756 --> 16:47.757
Come on.

16:47.966 --> 16:50.093
Move around a bit.
It's good for you.

16:50.427 --> 16:52.387
What? No.

16:52.762 --> 16:56.099
- Come on. Come on.
- Stop it.

16:57.767 --> 17:01.813
You need to occupy your mind. When
Dad died, you were gonna do things.

17:02.063 --> 17:05.942
- He was a saint.
- I know he was. But he's gone.

17:06.192 --> 17:09.070
You were gonna travel, volunteer.
You've done nothing.

17:09.279 --> 17:12.282
Stop telling me how to live my life.
Just shut up.

17:13.116 --> 17:14.284
I just worry...

17:14.492 --> 17:17.454
And don't start with that
nursing home business again.

17:17.620 --> 17:21.499
It's not a nursing home,
it's a retirement community!

17:21.791 --> 17:25.420
You interact with seniors
your own age, go places, do things!

17:25.628 --> 17:28.006
I've seen women in nursing homes...

17:28.256 --> 17:30.967
...in these wheelchairs,
babbling like idiots!

17:31.217 --> 17:32.969
Here, eat your eggplant.

17:33.136 --> 17:35.305
I told you, I already ate lunch.

17:39.017 --> 17:40.310
All right, listen.

17:41.352 --> 17:44.272
You just speak to Uncle Junior
about Artie, okay?

17:44.481 --> 17:46.316
He respects you.
He'll listen to you.

17:46.483 --> 17:51.321
If your uncle has business with Arthur,
he knows what he's doing.

17:54.866 --> 17:55.950
And I don't?

17:58.036 --> 18:00.747
Well, all I know is...

18:00.997 --> 18:03.875
...daughters are better at taking care
of their mothers than sons.

18:04.167 --> 18:07.003
Yeah, and I bought CDs
for a broken record.

18:12.008 --> 18:15.553
I expect to see you at Anthony Jr.'s
party with your baked ziti.

18:15.845 --> 18:18.807
Only if I'm picked up
and I'm brought back home.

18:19.015 --> 18:22.393
I don't drive
when they're predicting rain.

18:22.685 --> 18:24.979
You're healthy.
It's good for you to drive.

18:25.188 --> 18:27.398
Use it or lose it.
I gotta go to work.

18:27.857 --> 18:29.025
Sure...

18:29.692 --> 18:31.027
...run off!

18:33.404 --> 18:35.698
And that night was
my son's birthday party.

18:35.865 --> 18:38.701
<i>My wife invites the priest.
He's always at the house.</i>

18:38.868 --> 18:40.161
- Hey, Tony.
- How you doing?

18:40.370 --> 18:42.747
- You like <i>crème anglaise?</i>
- You bless it, I'll eat it.

18:42.914 --> 18:43.915
She's not coming.

18:44.207 --> 18:46.000
- Who?
- Grandma just called.

18:46.209 --> 18:48.419
She started crying and hung up.

18:48.670 --> 18:51.422
- She needs a purpose.
- She's tougher than you think.

18:51.714 --> 18:54.092
- So, what? No fucking ziti now?
- Hey!

19:25.707 --> 19:27.750
<i>At first it felt like...</i>

19:27.959 --> 19:29.919
<i>...ginger ale in my skull.</i>

19:40.597 --> 19:44.142
- Mom, Daddy just fell! Mom!
- Oh, my God. Tony!

19:47.270 --> 19:48.563
Get back!

19:49.772 --> 19:51.900
Daddy! Dad!

19:52.442 --> 19:54.611
Anthony Jr., call 911.

20:07.916 --> 20:11.920
<i>Dr. Cusamano put me in the
hospital, gave me every kind of test.</i>

20:22.639 --> 20:23.640
Okay.

20:28.144 --> 20:30.146
Hey! Carm.

20:33.650 --> 20:36.945
- Thought you might want some company.
- Yeah.

20:38.613 --> 20:40.490
6:30 in the morning.

20:42.992 --> 20:46.120
- How are the kids?
- They're worried about you.

20:47.163 --> 20:50.291
I told Anthony Jr.
We'd rain-check his birthday.

20:58.925 --> 21:00.176
Think I got a brain tumor?

21:00.927 --> 21:02.512
Well, we're gonna find out.

21:02.720 --> 21:05.682
What a bedside manner.
Very encouraging.

21:05.932 --> 21:07.558
What, are you gonna not know?

21:12.230 --> 21:15.149
We had some good times.
Had some good years.

21:15.358 --> 21:17.318
Here he goes with the nostalgia.

21:17.527 --> 21:19.362
No marriage is perfect.

21:19.529 --> 21:21.364
Having that <i>goomar</i> on the side helps.

21:21.572 --> 21:25.201
I'm not seeing her anymore.
What about that priest?

21:25.451 --> 21:26.828
Don't even go there.

21:27.036 --> 21:30.748
Father is a spiritual mentor.
He's making me a better Catholic!

21:30.999 --> 21:33.710
Well, we all got different needs.

21:33.960 --> 21:37.714
What's different between us is,
you're going to hell when you die.

21:56.399 --> 22:00.778
<i>My nephew, Christopher, was
handling the garbage contract problem.</i>

22:01.029 --> 22:03.906
<i>But on this I will also
not go into detail.</i>

22:20.423 --> 22:22.633
Emil Kolar.

22:23.092 --> 22:24.886
Chris Moltisanti.

22:25.762 --> 22:28.723
Hey, in Czech Republic too,
we love pork.

22:29.098 --> 22:30.808
You ever have our sausages?

22:31.100 --> 22:35.605
No. I thought the only sausages
they had was Italian and Jimmy Dean's.

22:36.105 --> 22:39.108
See what you learn when you
cross cultures and shit?

22:40.818 --> 22:43.279
My Uncle Evzen doesn't know I came.

22:43.571 --> 22:45.948
If we make any progress,
I'll tell him.

22:46.157 --> 22:50.161
Hey, we have to make progress, Emil.
We gotta stop the madness.

22:50.411 --> 22:53.331
Business is changing,
we're the younger generation.

22:53.623 --> 22:55.124
We have issues in common.

22:56.459 --> 22:57.919
Emil.

22:59.253 --> 23:02.298
Where'd you go to high school?
Was it Poland?

23:03.633 --> 23:04.842
I'm not Polish.

23:05.134 --> 23:08.137
Czechoslovakian,
that's a type of Polack, right?

23:08.346 --> 23:11.766
We came here when I was 9.
I went to West Essex.

23:11.974 --> 23:15.144
You used to play my cousin Gregory
in football, he...

23:15.353 --> 23:18.439
- Where's the stuff?
- Yes, yes, yes.

23:20.691 --> 23:24.612
The reason for the visit.
We got it all deployed for you.

23:25.988 --> 23:27.824
Taste the wares, Emil.

23:28.616 --> 23:29.992
Emil.

23:54.517 --> 23:59.397
The doctors kept me hanging
about the tests, as doctors will do.

23:59.814 --> 24:03.359
So my uncle and I played
a round of golf and had lunch.

24:03.609 --> 24:07.029
You keep mentioning your uncle.
What's the problem?

24:07.697 --> 24:08.698
Who do you think you are?

24:08.990 --> 24:12.160
I'm the person who says
how things go, that's who.

24:12.368 --> 24:16.205
Artie's dinner business is nice,
upscale people from the suburbs.

24:16.497 --> 24:17.832
Don't ruin his life.

24:18.040 --> 24:20.877
Vesuvio is where Pussy feels safe.

24:21.127 --> 24:23.629
He's been eating here all his life.

24:23.880 --> 24:25.715
You kill him someplace else.

24:25.923 --> 24:29.051
You may run North Jersey,
but you don't run your uncle!

24:29.343 --> 24:32.763
How many fucking hours did I spend
playing catch with you?

24:37.185 --> 24:40.730
<i>Can we focus more
on your immediate family?</i>

24:41.731 --> 24:44.692
<i>My wife and daughter
were not getting along.</i>

24:47.445 --> 24:50.281
Darn, these laser discs
are incredible!

24:51.032 --> 24:56.078
Tony watches <i>Godfather II</i>. He says
it looks just like the movie theater.

24:56.287 --> 24:58.664
Gordon Willis.
Tony prefers <i>II,</i> not <i>I?</i>

24:58.915 --> 25:01.584
He likes where Vito
goes back to Sicily.

25:01.792 --> 25:04.086
With <i>III,</i> he was like,
"What happened?"

25:04.253 --> 25:05.671
Where does Tony rank <i>Goodfellas?</i>

25:08.257 --> 25:10.092
What, do you have raccoons?

25:10.801 --> 25:12.970
- Somebody's jimmying a window.
- What?

25:13.221 --> 25:16.599
You have all these security
lights, who would try and...?

25:17.475 --> 25:20.269
Oh, no. Jeez, Louise!

25:21.062 --> 25:22.271
Hold it!

25:22.730 --> 25:23.940
Meadow.

25:25.441 --> 25:29.612
I noticed the glass rattles every time
I walk to the laundry room.

25:29.779 --> 25:31.614
Do we have any putty?

25:31.781 --> 25:33.991
Don't give me that.
You snuck out!

25:34.242 --> 25:35.451
What's going on?

25:35.701 --> 25:38.079
You locked my bedroom window
so I'd get caught.

25:38.287 --> 25:41.457
Normal people thought you were
upstairs doing your homework!

25:41.707 --> 25:45.294
You have become a master
of lying and conniving.

25:45.503 --> 25:47.129
I know I'm grounded.

25:47.421 --> 25:50.091
Patrick's swim meet is tomorrow,
and he needed me!

25:50.299 --> 25:53.469
Grounded for this?
Oh, no, you're not grounded.

25:53.719 --> 25:57.848
You're not going to Aspen
with Hunter Scangarelo!

25:58.474 --> 25:59.642
Yes!

25:59.976 --> 26:01.769
But this shit I'm telling you...

26:01.978 --> 26:04.146
...it'll all blow over.

26:06.107 --> 26:11.237
Didn't you admit to Dr. Cusamano
that you were feeling depressed?

26:23.249 --> 26:24.500
"Melfi."

26:26.294 --> 26:27.837
What part of the boot you from?

26:28.170 --> 26:30.006
Dr. Melfi.

26:30.798 --> 26:33.467
My father's people were from Caserta.

26:33.676 --> 26:35.177
Avellino.

26:35.386 --> 26:38.514
My mother would have loved it
if you and I got together.

26:45.354 --> 26:50.026
Anxiety attacks are legitimate
psychiatric emergencies.

26:50.192 --> 26:52.528
Suppose you were driving
and you passed out.

26:52.778 --> 26:54.196
Let me tell you something.

26:54.488 --> 26:57.533
Nowadays, everybody's gotta go
to shrinks and counselors...

26:57.825 --> 27:01.329
...and go on <i>Sally Jessy Raphael</i>
and talk about their problems.

27:01.537 --> 27:04.206
Whatever happened to Gary Cooper?

27:04.498 --> 27:06.709
The strong, silent type?

27:07.001 --> 27:08.377
That was an American.

27:08.586 --> 27:11.297
He wasn't in touch
with his feelings.

27:11.547 --> 27:15.217
They didn't realize once they got Gary
Cooper in touch with his feelings...

27:15.426 --> 27:16.886
...they wouldn't be able
to shut him up!

27:17.178 --> 27:20.097
So it's dysfunction this and
that! And dysfunction <i>va fangool!</i>

27:21.557 --> 27:23.392
You have strong feelings about this.

27:23.601 --> 27:27.188
I had a semester and a half
of college...

27:27.396 --> 27:30.900
...so I understand Freud.
I understand therapy as a concept.

27:31.108 --> 27:33.819
But in my world, it does not go down.

27:34.070 --> 27:37.740
Could I be happier?
Yeah. Yeah. Who couldn't?

27:38.908 --> 27:40.409
Do you feel depressed?

27:43.454 --> 27:45.456
Do you feel depressed?

27:51.212 --> 27:53.214
Since the ducks left...

27:54.423 --> 27:55.716
I guess.

27:56.425 --> 27:59.595
The ducks that preceded
your losing consciousness.

27:59.929 --> 28:02.139
Let's talk about them.

28:15.611 --> 28:18.906
You can't blame T for being pissed.
You should have waited.

28:19.115 --> 28:21.617
That's the last time I show
any fucking initiative.

28:21.867 --> 28:23.953
Imagine how I felt?

28:24.286 --> 28:25.746
T's running down the business...

28:25.955 --> 28:28.290
...I fucking wet a guy
to keep one of our stops.

28:28.499 --> 28:31.961
He's not running it down.
It's just getting harder in New York.

28:33.754 --> 28:35.131
One.

28:35.423 --> 28:36.632
Two.

28:36.924 --> 28:38.259
Three.

28:39.009 --> 28:40.469
Come on!

28:40.886 --> 28:43.305
- This is fucked up.
- What, Pussy?

28:43.514 --> 28:47.101
The Kolar uncle is gonna find the kid
dead on one of his bins...

28:47.309 --> 28:49.937
...and get out of our
fucking business? No way.

28:50.146 --> 28:52.189
"Louis Brassi sleeps with the fishes."

28:53.774 --> 28:55.609
Luca Brassi.

28:55.818 --> 28:57.319
- Luca.
- Whatever.

28:58.320 --> 29:00.406
There's differences, Christopher.

29:00.656 --> 29:03.325
From the Luca Brassi situation
and this?

29:05.327 --> 29:09.206
Look, if the Kolars know the kid is
dead, it hardens their position.

29:09.498 --> 29:13.127
Plus, now the cops are looking
for a fucking murderer.

29:13.335 --> 29:14.670
What do you want to do?

29:15.129 --> 29:18.007
He disappears.
He never comes home.

29:18.340 --> 29:20.342
They know, but they don't know.

29:20.551 --> 29:23.929
They hope maybe he'll turn up... if.

29:25.806 --> 29:27.641
Come on. Let's get him.

29:28.184 --> 29:29.477
Got him?

29:29.685 --> 29:32.229
Take him to Staten Island,
I'll cut him up.

29:32.521 --> 29:35.858
Pussy, you know, with T
collapsing at the birthday...

29:36.066 --> 29:39.987
...what would you do
if he was, like, disabled?

29:40.196 --> 29:41.989
Why would you even ask that?

29:44.658 --> 29:46.702
Our lecture series in action.

29:46.952 --> 29:48.746
Someone from the university
discussing...

29:49.038 --> 29:52.249
...the novels of, I believe,
Zora Neale Hurston.

29:54.168 --> 29:56.670
Didn't you just read her
in school, Med?

29:57.880 --> 29:59.381
It's very nice.

30:05.387 --> 30:07.723
You know, Grandma,
this place is neat.

30:07.973 --> 30:09.892
You should really think about it.

30:10.559 --> 30:13.229
This room was renovated last year.

30:13.521 --> 30:14.980
What goes on behind there?

30:15.606 --> 30:18.108
Those doors lead to our nursing unit.

30:19.610 --> 30:21.237
This is a nursing home!

30:21.529 --> 30:23.405
This is a residence,
but just in case...

30:23.614 --> 30:26.742
No, you're not getting me
into a nursing home.

30:26.992 --> 30:28.786
You're not listening
to what she's saying.

30:29.078 --> 30:31.288
Women in wheelchairs,
babbling like idiots!

30:31.580 --> 30:33.123
Ma, you're not listening.

30:33.374 --> 30:36.377
You think you're so high and mighty,
don't you?

30:36.585 --> 30:39.088
With your fancy office.

30:39.588 --> 30:42.550
Anthony, people come here to die!

30:46.512 --> 30:51.267
Oh, my God! Somebody get a doctor.

30:59.024 --> 31:04.113
So you've come back for help.
Don't look at that as a defeat.

31:04.530 --> 31:07.324
She's one of those who grew up
during the Depression.

31:07.616 --> 31:10.452
But the Depression to her
was a trip to Six Flags.

31:10.661 --> 31:12.288
There's that "D" word again.

31:18.836 --> 31:20.754
Stay with your mother.

31:25.175 --> 31:28.762
Now that my father's dead,
he's a saint.

31:29.555 --> 31:32.933
When he was alive, nothing.

31:37.313 --> 31:40.649
My dad was tough, he ran his own crew.

31:41.317 --> 31:45.446
A guy like that and my mother
wore him down to a little nub.

31:45.654 --> 31:48.782
He was a squeaking little gerbil
when he died.

31:50.326 --> 31:53.662
Quite a formidable maternal presence.

31:57.374 --> 32:02.504
I gotta be honest. I'm not getting
any satisfaction from my work, either.

32:02.671 --> 32:04.006
Why?

32:05.883 --> 32:07.343
Well, because of RICO.

32:07.885 --> 32:10.804
- Is he your brother?
- No. The RICO Statutes.

32:11.013 --> 32:12.348
Oh, of course, right.

32:12.514 --> 32:13.515
You read the papers?

32:13.682 --> 32:15.851
You know, the government's using
electronic surveillance...

32:16.143 --> 32:20.606
...and various legal strategies
to squeeze my business.

32:23.192 --> 32:28.155
Do you have any qualms about
how you actually make a living?

32:29.531 --> 32:30.741
Yeah.

32:32.701 --> 32:35.245
I find I have to be the sad clown.

32:35.704 --> 32:38.624
Laughing on the outside...

32:38.874 --> 32:40.501
...crying on the inside.

32:40.709 --> 32:43.212
See, things are trending downward.

32:44.880 --> 32:47.841
Used to be, a guy got pinched,
he took his prison jolt.

32:48.217 --> 32:50.719
Everybody upheld a code of silence.

32:50.928 --> 32:54.223
Nowadays, no values.

32:54.640 --> 32:57.726
Guys today have no room
for the penal experience.

32:57.935 --> 33:00.062
So everybody turns government witness.

33:04.233 --> 33:06.944
I feel exhausted
just talking about it.

33:07.861 --> 33:12.574
Well, with today's pharmacology,
no one needs to suffer...

33:12.866 --> 33:16.370
...with feelings of
exhaustion and depression.

33:17.454 --> 33:21.125
Here we go.
Here comes the Prozac.

33:29.800 --> 33:30.968
Mahaffey doesn't have it.

33:31.260 --> 33:32.928
What do you mean
he doesn't have it?

33:33.178 --> 33:34.263
He doesn't have the money.

33:34.430 --> 33:35.764
How can he not have the money?

33:35.973 --> 33:38.267
The man does not have the money.

33:38.475 --> 33:40.936
We ran the man over with the car.
T, himself.

33:41.186 --> 33:44.481
The man has no wiggle room.
He's bled dry.

33:49.194 --> 33:50.446
So...

33:51.572 --> 33:54.241
...I hear Junior wants to
whack Pussy Bompensiero?

33:54.450 --> 33:57.119
- Pussy Malanga.
- Oh, Little Pussy.

33:57.327 --> 33:59.621
You think he's gonna
fuck with Big Pussy?

33:59.913 --> 34:01.415
My Pussy?

34:02.249 --> 34:03.459
Andrea.

34:05.627 --> 34:08.297
Stay with drinks on the house
all night.

34:08.756 --> 34:11.133
- Sorry, Mr. Dante.
- It's okay.

34:12.092 --> 34:16.305
So your uncle resents
that you're the boss.

34:16.597 --> 34:18.140
The sadness accrues.

34:19.141 --> 34:21.143
Your uncle's had a hard-on
his whole life.

34:21.351 --> 34:23.520
First, against your father,
his younger brother...

34:23.812 --> 34:25.606
...because he was a made man
before him.

34:25.814 --> 34:27.483
And now, you.

34:27.858 --> 34:31.653
So, sure, he can't stomach
your telling him what to do.

34:32.112 --> 34:34.156
Hesh, I love the man.

34:34.323 --> 34:38.118
The man is driven <i>in toto</i>
by his insecurities.

34:38.327 --> 34:40.621
I feel bad I was the messenger.

34:42.873 --> 34:45.250
Your friend Artie,
with the restaurant.

34:45.459 --> 34:47.127
Get him out of town.

34:47.336 --> 34:51.757
That way the restaurant closes,
the hit goes down someplace else.

34:54.343 --> 34:55.636
You old fucking Jew.

34:55.844 --> 34:58.138
No wonder my old man
kept you around so long.

34:58.347 --> 35:01.850
So what about this fucking Jew's
250 on Mahaffey's 100?

35:06.313 --> 35:08.774
Mahaffey has a new business partner...

35:09.024 --> 35:10.275
...you.

35:10.526 --> 35:12.361
These HMOs pay out millions...

35:12.569 --> 35:15.155
...to doctors, hospitals, whatever.

35:15.489 --> 35:18.492
That MRI I had,
$2000 a pop.

35:18.700 --> 35:20.994
Now, we give this Mahaffey a choice.

35:21.203 --> 35:23.580
Either his company pays out
phony claims...

35:23.872 --> 35:26.041
...to fake clinics we set up...

35:27.000 --> 35:30.712
...or he pays Hesh
the 250 grand he owes him...

35:30.921 --> 35:33.173
...which we know he cannot do.

35:36.301 --> 35:38.554
Or it's a rainy night in Lyndhurst.

35:40.055 --> 35:43.100
Very smart.
Could be major.

35:43.809 --> 35:45.561
Could be as good as garbage.

35:45.894 --> 35:49.731
- Garbage is our bread and butter.
- Was.

36:00.117 --> 36:02.119
Miss Meadow!

36:05.080 --> 36:06.540
So, Med.

36:07.040 --> 36:09.251
I'm not going.

36:09.751 --> 36:13.589
Every year, on this date,
since you were itty-bitty...

36:13.881 --> 36:15.924
...Mom and Meadow get all dolled up...

36:16.091 --> 36:21.096
...drive into New York Plaza Hotel
for tea under Eloise's portrait.

36:21.346 --> 36:22.973
Look, where's yours?

36:23.223 --> 36:24.725
I have too much homework.

36:24.933 --> 36:27.102
Meadow, its our little tradition!

36:27.352 --> 36:28.937
We always have so much fun!

36:29.146 --> 36:32.441
To tell you the truth,
I felt it was dumb since I was 8!

36:32.649 --> 36:35.068
I just go because you like it.

36:38.405 --> 36:42.784
Here I thought this was something we
would do long after you got married...

36:43.285 --> 36:44.912
...with girls of your own.

36:45.120 --> 36:46.872
Hopefully I won't be
living around here by then.

36:47.039 --> 36:49.124
<i>You've got mail.</i>

36:50.792 --> 36:55.923
Meadow, you can't just lie and cheat
and break the rules you don't like!

36:58.508 --> 37:01.136
What? You have something
you want to say?

37:02.304 --> 37:06.600
Mom, do you have any idea how much
it means to go skiing in Aspen?

37:07.100 --> 37:09.269
Do you think that'll
happen every year?

37:09.478 --> 37:12.940
Like lame tea and scones
at the Plaza Hotel?

37:15.525 --> 37:18.487
- Goodbye.
- Close my door, please.

37:19.988 --> 37:21.198
Artie.

37:21.490 --> 37:26.161
Give me a drop. Oh! A drop,
not a spurt. <i>Soave,</i> a drop!

37:27.663 --> 37:29.790
- How are you?
- All right. Stir the meatballs.

37:29.998 --> 37:32.668
- Could you help me out?
- Yeah, what do you need?

37:33.502 --> 37:34.836
Cruise. Caribbean.

37:35.045 --> 37:38.006
<i>S.S. Sagafjord,</i> 11th through the 29th.

37:38.173 --> 37:40.425
Pair of tickets. I can't use them.

37:40.676 --> 37:42.511
Can you take them off my hands?

37:42.719 --> 37:44.805
- Where'd they come from?
- Comps.

37:45.847 --> 37:47.224
Comps?

37:47.557 --> 37:48.850
What does that mean?

37:49.017 --> 37:51.853
As manager for the Kitchen
and Restaurant Workers Union...

37:52.020 --> 37:55.482
...I administer the dental plan.
You listening to me?

37:55.691 --> 37:59.361
A couple of dentists got together
and awarded me these tickets.

37:59.569 --> 38:02.364
The problem is,
I can't get away those dates.

38:05.367 --> 38:08.036
Here. When was your last vacation?

38:08.245 --> 38:10.872
- Anthony, thank you.
- All right.

38:18.213 --> 38:19.881
Mr. Soprano?

38:27.723 --> 38:31.226
You cannot accept a gift
like that from Tony Soprano! No way!

38:31.518 --> 38:32.728
Listen to me, Charmaine...

38:33.020 --> 38:36.356
...if I stick my hand up the ass of
one more lobster without a break...

38:36.565 --> 38:37.858
...I'm gonna go postal.

38:38.066 --> 38:41.403
I don't even want to talk about it
anymore, please!

38:41.611 --> 38:45.699
Art, Melissa, come on, honey.
It's time to go home.

38:45.907 --> 38:50.245
You have to get away.
We have to get away for the marriage.

38:50.495 --> 38:55.500
No! It's bad enough that these
mobsters patronize the place, okay?

38:55.751 --> 38:57.502
So what? We're not connected.

38:57.711 --> 39:00.714
Right. Because we just
turned down those tickets!

39:00.922 --> 39:04.634
But the tickets were comps.
Tony is a labor leader.

39:04.926 --> 39:06.553
Arthur, please. Grow up!

39:06.762 --> 39:10.599
Does the mind not rebel at any
scenario under which dentists...

39:10.807 --> 39:15.520
...are sending the don of New Jersey
first class on a Norwegian steamship?

39:15.771 --> 39:19.608
Come on, Arthur, somebody donated
their kneecaps for those tickets!

39:20.317 --> 39:23.820
Herman, there is no way I can
subvert my fucking company.

39:24.112 --> 39:27.157
Have them pay claims for MRIs
that never happened?

39:27.449 --> 39:30.911
- The paperwork will look real.
- How do I not get caught?

39:31.119 --> 39:34.289
I hate to hear you knocking yourself.
You're a smart guy.

39:34.539 --> 39:38.251
I'm depressed. I'm so fucking
depressed I can't eat, sleep.

39:38.460 --> 39:41.296
- You on Prozac?
- Zoloft. It's similar.

39:41.546 --> 39:43.840
- It's supposed to help with gambling.
- No shit.

39:44.132 --> 39:46.343
This new generation
of antidepressants...

39:46.635 --> 39:49.596
...are supposed to be useful
against compulsive behaviors.

39:49.805 --> 39:51.098
That's a shame.

39:51.306 --> 39:53.850
A medication comes along
after your gambling...

39:54.142 --> 39:56.478
...gets your fucking hip
busted to shit.

39:56.645 --> 39:58.939
I'm trying not to be cynical.

39:59.147 --> 40:03.068
Your debt and the feelings surrounding
it is the source of all your problems.

40:03.318 --> 40:05.821
I'm sorry I haven't paid you, Herman.

40:06.071 --> 40:07.489
I know you are.

40:07.697 --> 40:09.950
And I never meant to
denigrate Tony Soprano.

40:10.158 --> 40:12.702
- Want to walk on the rocks?
- Crutches, I can't.

40:12.994 --> 40:15.956
It's beautiful out there.
Come on, we'll help you.

40:16.164 --> 40:17.833
I go out there to think.

40:32.806 --> 40:34.182
Thanks, but no.

40:36.977 --> 40:38.353
Let's try it.

40:38.645 --> 40:42.357
What you were saying before
with the MRIs and...

41:04.212 --> 41:05.547
T!

41:07.132 --> 41:09.134
Dick's looking for you!

41:10.844 --> 41:13.889
Hey, Tony, I just heard
from Triborough Towers.

41:14.181 --> 41:17.225
The Kolar brothers withdrew their bid.

41:17.517 --> 41:18.727
That's good. That's good.

41:19.019 --> 41:21.897
Listen, by the way,
Artie Bucco's here to see you.

41:22.397 --> 41:24.441
- I gotta go, guys.
- Take care.

41:30.655 --> 41:32.073
Artie!

41:32.866 --> 41:34.367
Artie, you all right?

41:37.078 --> 41:39.206
- I can't.
- What are you talking about?

41:39.414 --> 41:42.292
We discussed this.
You gotta leave town.

41:42.584 --> 41:43.793
I'm sorry.

41:52.093 --> 41:53.303
This is unacceptable.

41:53.553 --> 41:55.805
I made a reservation two weeks ago.

41:56.056 --> 42:00.060
Sir, people are not leaving, and there
are five parties ahead of you.

42:00.268 --> 42:02.938
- So what would you like...?
- Can I help you?

42:05.482 --> 42:07.442
I tore her a new one.

42:08.485 --> 42:11.446
Why don't we just go
to another restaurant and eat?

42:11.696 --> 42:12.948
We're here.

42:13.240 --> 42:15.617
Mr. Soprano, how you doing?
Good to see you.

42:15.825 --> 42:17.285
How you doing?

42:17.452 --> 42:19.204
<i>- Signora.</i>
- Hello.

42:19.454 --> 42:21.289
This way. Excuse me.

42:25.502 --> 42:30.006
Sweetie-pie, I'm hungry.
Tony, where you going?

42:30.298 --> 42:31.967
Hey. How are you?

42:32.217 --> 42:33.635
Good.

42:35.303 --> 42:36.638
You come here?

42:36.846 --> 42:38.598
When possible.

42:39.474 --> 42:43.770
Those decorating tips you gave me,
they really work.

42:44.729 --> 42:45.981
Good.

42:47.816 --> 42:48.984
How you doing?

42:53.822 --> 42:55.490
Nils, Nils?

42:55.657 --> 42:57.284
Do you know who that was?

42:57.492 --> 43:00.161
Well, I mean, obviously you do.

43:00.453 --> 43:01.997
What, is he a patient?

43:02.247 --> 43:03.623
You know I can't say.

43:08.044 --> 43:10.380
Decorating tips, yeah, right.

43:10.672 --> 43:12.674
Nils, shut the fuck up.

43:12.882 --> 43:15.885
Mr. Borglund, they're setting up
your table now.

43:17.846 --> 43:19.014
Whoa.

43:20.515 --> 43:22.851
Who was that woman at the restaurant?

43:23.059 --> 43:24.519
My decorator.

43:24.769 --> 43:27.188
What?
You're redoing the garbage dump?

43:27.355 --> 43:30.692
That's funny. Hey, you better
not mess with that hat!

43:34.279 --> 43:37.032
Come on, it's JFK's hat!
I bought it at that auction.

43:37.282 --> 43:38.408
Give me that!

43:39.868 --> 43:41.369
Irina, Jesus.

43:41.828 --> 43:45.707
I know there is something more
intimate between you and her.

43:46.207 --> 43:48.209
Nothing intimate. We just talk.

43:58.428 --> 44:00.180
Mr. Soprano, <i>buona sera.</i>

44:00.388 --> 44:02.390
We don't see you.
Where you been?

44:09.064 --> 44:10.940
You know, sometimes...

44:12.067 --> 44:13.401
...life is good.

44:13.610 --> 44:15.570
Life is often good.

44:16.905 --> 44:19.074
Regaleali, for example.

44:20.909 --> 44:23.203
You've been in good spirits
the last couple days.

44:32.087 --> 44:36.091
Carmela, there's something
I gotta confess.

44:39.844 --> 44:41.096
What are you doing?

44:41.346 --> 44:44.099
Getting my wine in position
to throw in your face!

44:44.265 --> 44:45.600
You're always with the drama.

44:45.767 --> 44:48.228
Confess already, please.
Get it over with!

44:53.274 --> 44:54.776
I'm on Prozac.

44:56.152 --> 44:57.612
Oh. Oh, my God.

44:58.405 --> 45:00.156
I been seeing a therapist.

45:00.448 --> 45:03.118
Oh, my God.
I think that's great.

45:03.368 --> 45:06.413
I think that's wonderful!
I think that's so gutsy!

45:06.621 --> 45:09.416
- Take it easy.
- But I think that's very wonderful.

45:09.624 --> 45:11.584
You'd think I was Hannibal Lecter.

45:11.793 --> 45:14.421
I think it's great.
Psychology doesn't address the soul.

45:14.629 --> 45:16.464
But this is a start.
This is something.

45:16.673 --> 45:18.591
Oh, I'm gonna shut up now.

45:19.134 --> 45:20.635
I'll shut up now.

45:21.469 --> 45:22.929
You're the only person who knows.

45:23.138 --> 45:26.015
The only reason I'm telling you this
is because you're my wife.

45:26.307 --> 45:29.644
You're the only person on this planet
that I'm completely honest with.

45:29.894 --> 45:31.646
Oh, please.

45:31.813 --> 45:33.481
Hey, goddamn it, I'm serious.

45:33.815 --> 45:35.984
If the wrong person finds out,
I get a steel jacket...

45:36.276 --> 45:38.528
...of antidepressant
in the back of the head.

45:48.121 --> 45:50.665
I didn't realize you were so unhappy.

45:54.669 --> 45:55.962
I don't know.

45:56.546 --> 45:58.173
My mother...

45:58.423 --> 46:00.216
You told him about your father, right?

46:00.508 --> 46:03.178
- Who?
- Your therapist.

46:04.512 --> 46:06.681
Yeah. Yeah, I told him.

46:06.848 --> 46:10.685
Good. But your mother is the one.

46:11.519 --> 46:16.024
I don't know, I just feel like lately
my life's out of balance.

46:18.860 --> 46:22.363
Our existence on this earth
is a puzzle.

46:23.364 --> 46:25.325
My own daughter hates me.

46:26.493 --> 46:28.203
She doesn't hate you, Carm.

46:28.495 --> 46:30.205
We were best friends.

46:30.455 --> 46:33.666
Mothers and their daughters.
She'll come back to you.

46:38.671 --> 46:39.881
- Hello?
<i>- Jesus!</i>

46:40.089 --> 46:42.050
What's the matter, no social life?

46:42.217 --> 46:43.718
Blow me.

46:45.053 --> 46:46.346
Dad.

46:46.554 --> 46:49.891
I brought you my primavera.
It's your favorite.

46:51.392 --> 46:52.894
- Who is it?
- Christopher.

46:53.102 --> 46:55.522
- Hey.
- Our friend is back in town.

46:55.730 --> 47:00.527
<i>"Little Pussy" Malanga,
confused with "Big Pussy" Bompensiero...</i>

47:01.277 --> 47:02.612
<i>...had just returned from Florida...</i>

47:02.904 --> 47:04.864
So it's gonna go down soon?

47:05.073 --> 47:07.075
Don't worry.
I got a way to put it to bed.

47:08.910 --> 47:10.537
Come on, Meadow.

47:11.246 --> 47:14.082
- Go, Falcons!
- Come on, let's go!

47:14.999 --> 47:17.210
So when do you need this by?

47:17.418 --> 47:18.878
Right away.

47:19.420 --> 47:22.590
- Way to go, Meadow!
- Beautiful, beautiful!

47:23.258 --> 47:25.426
I think I can get a party
like that together.

47:25.760 --> 47:29.264
- Side out? That ball hit the line!
- What are you doing, ref?

47:33.810 --> 47:35.144
Mom didn't come?

47:35.436 --> 47:37.438
Didn't think you wanted her to.

47:38.106 --> 47:39.774
The car's over there.

47:40.024 --> 47:42.610
Hey, Mr. Dante.
See you, Heather.

47:43.820 --> 47:45.405
You guys played a good game.

47:45.613 --> 47:47.448
Heather Dante.
Where'd she get that spike?

47:47.657 --> 47:50.410
Don't you think it's
unfair what Mom is doing?

47:50.618 --> 47:53.079
Making this little
movie scene out of it.

47:53.288 --> 47:57.041
"The Sad Mom Who Can't Even Come
to Her Daughter's Sports Event."

48:03.464 --> 48:04.799
Dad?

48:05.466 --> 48:07.468
Don't you think it's
totally out there?

48:07.635 --> 48:11.639
I mean, my Aspen trip.
What is she thinking?

48:12.640 --> 48:14.100
Dad?

48:19.939 --> 48:22.275
It's been years since I've been here.

48:22.650 --> 48:25.069
Dad, please talk to her, please.

48:25.361 --> 48:28.072
God, this is so stupid.

48:28.990 --> 48:30.491
Why are we sitting here?

48:32.201 --> 48:35.371
Your mother thinks you have the
capacity to be a top student.

48:35.622 --> 48:36.831
And I agree.

48:37.081 --> 48:38.833
What do you guys want, perfection?

48:41.961 --> 48:43.671
What are you looking at?

48:44.172 --> 48:47.675
Your great-grandfather
and his brother Frank...

48:48.509 --> 48:50.178
...they built this place.

48:50.845 --> 48:52.096
Big whoop.

48:52.347 --> 48:55.516
Stone and marble workers.
They came over here from Italy...

48:56.351 --> 48:58.519
...and they built this place.

48:59.812 --> 49:02.357
Yeah, right. Two guys.

49:03.608 --> 49:08.529
No, they were two guys on a crew of,
you know, laborers.

49:10.865 --> 49:13.618
They didn't design it...

49:13.868 --> 49:16.037
...but they knew how to build it.

49:18.539 --> 49:21.376
Now find two guys who can
put decent grout around your bathtub.

49:59.038 --> 50:00.415
So I feel good.

50:00.665 --> 50:04.043
So I don't know if I'm
gonna be needing to come back.

50:04.544 --> 50:06.421
It's not the Prozac.

50:06.963 --> 50:08.256
Why not?

50:08.464 --> 50:13.594
You said you're thinking clearer and
your wife says you seem to be better?

50:15.096 --> 50:16.931
It's not the medication.

50:18.766 --> 50:22.729
Prozac takes weeks to build up
effective levels in the blood.

50:24.272 --> 50:25.606
Well, what is it, then?

50:26.816 --> 50:29.068
Coming here. Talking.

50:30.403 --> 50:32.780
Hope comes in many forms.

50:33.197 --> 50:35.116
Well, who's got time for that?

50:35.742 --> 50:37.744
What is it you want to say to me?

50:47.253 --> 50:49.297
I had a dream last night.

50:52.091 --> 50:53.468
Uh...

50:55.803 --> 50:58.014
My bellybutton was...

50:59.348 --> 51:01.142
...a Phillips head screw...

51:01.851 --> 51:04.312
...and I'm working unscrewing it...

51:05.104 --> 51:06.981
...and when I get it unscrewed...

51:09.650 --> 51:11.486
...my penis falls off.

51:16.491 --> 51:20.161
You know, I pick it up and I'm holding
it and I'm running around...

51:20.369 --> 51:23.831
...looking for the guy who used to
work on my Lincoln...

51:24.040 --> 51:26.501
...so he can put it back on.

51:26.834 --> 51:29.962
And you know, I'm holding it up...

51:30.171 --> 51:34.133
...and this bird swoops down
and grabs it in its beak...

51:35.176 --> 51:36.969
...and flies off with it.

51:41.516 --> 51:43.017
What kind of bird?

51:44.852 --> 51:47.188
I don't know. Sea gull or something.

51:47.355 --> 51:48.773
A water bird?

51:50.024 --> 51:53.069
I saw <i>The Birds</i> last week.
Think that planted the idea?

51:53.319 --> 51:55.196
What else is a water bird?

51:56.322 --> 51:59.200
Pelican, flamingo.

51:59.992 --> 52:01.536
What about ducks?

52:08.292 --> 52:10.002
Those goddamn ducks.

52:10.211 --> 52:13.214
What is it about those ducks
that meant so much to you?

52:20.012 --> 52:22.098
I don't know, it was a trip...

52:22.348 --> 52:26.686
...having those wild creatures...

52:27.436 --> 52:30.898
...come into my pool
and have their little babies.

52:37.905 --> 52:39.824
I was sad to see them go.

52:41.909 --> 52:44.912
Oh, Jesus, fuck. Now he's gonna cry.

52:53.421 --> 52:55.423
Shit. Fuck me.

52:55.631 --> 53:00.761
When the ducks gave birth to those
babies, they became a family.

53:05.224 --> 53:06.642
You're right.

53:07.435 --> 53:09.937
It's a link. A connection.

53:10.730 --> 53:13.733
I'm afraid I'm gonna
lose my family...

53:13.941 --> 53:15.902
...like I lost the ducks.

53:18.279 --> 53:20.907
That's what I'm full of dread about.

53:23.117 --> 53:24.577
It's always with me.

53:24.785 --> 53:27.121
What are you so afraid's
going to happen?

53:28.456 --> 53:29.874
I don't know.

53:36.130 --> 53:37.381
You work so hard.

53:37.632 --> 53:41.969
You work so damn hard
and to see your life's dream...

53:43.304 --> 53:45.097
...burn down.

53:45.806 --> 53:48.267
Look at it this way,
you collect the insurance.

53:48.476 --> 53:51.604
You gotta say to yourself,
"It could have been worse."

53:51.812 --> 53:55.524
How could it have been worse?
Fucking faulty stove!

53:55.816 --> 53:58.819
Suppose people stopped coming,
ever think of that?

54:00.905 --> 54:03.157
I don't know.
I don't know what the fuck.

54:05.618 --> 54:07.828
He's right.
There's no insurance for that.

54:07.995 --> 54:12.708
Why would people stop coming to the
restaurant? It's just catching on.

54:13.960 --> 54:16.170
You know what I'm
figuring out lately?

54:17.630 --> 54:19.298
Talking helps.

54:19.507 --> 54:21.634
- That's right.
- He's right. He's right.

54:25.179 --> 54:28.349
Hope... comes in many forms.

54:28.933 --> 54:30.184
Absolutely.

54:30.643 --> 54:31.852
Come on.

54:33.688 --> 54:35.064
Here, hold this.

54:35.314 --> 54:36.565
Artie.

54:37.191 --> 54:38.859
Artie, come on.

54:39.151 --> 54:40.194
Hey, hey.

54:40.444 --> 54:42.863
Hey, look at me. Look at me.

54:43.698 --> 54:45.533
I'll always help you.

54:45.741 --> 54:48.202
Come on. Come on.

54:53.541 --> 54:56.335
Go cook. Hey, let him cook.
He'll feel better.

55:09.098 --> 55:12.226
Someday I'll tell him
we torched the restaurant.

55:17.732 --> 55:20.401
All right, enough of this shit.
What's wrong?

55:22.111 --> 55:23.404
You know, a simple...

55:23.612 --> 55:27.491
..."Way to go, Chris, on the Triborough
Towers contract!" would have been nice.

55:27.742 --> 55:29.076
That's it.

55:38.419 --> 55:39.628
You're right.

55:40.129 --> 55:41.505
You're right.

55:42.548 --> 55:44.133
I have no defense.

55:44.759 --> 55:49.138
That's how I was parented.
Never supported. Never complimented.

55:49.930 --> 55:51.557
My cousin Gregory's girlfriend...

55:51.766 --> 55:54.935
...is what they call a development
girl, out in Hollywood.

55:55.144 --> 55:57.897
She said I could sell my life story,
make fucking millions.

55:58.105 --> 56:00.900
I didn't do that.
I stuck it out with you.

56:01.108 --> 56:04.945
I'll fucking kill you.
Are you gonna go Henry Hill on me now?

56:05.321 --> 56:08.282
You know how many mobsters are selling
screenplays and screwing things up?

56:08.532 --> 56:10.659
She said I could maybe
even play myself.

56:10.951 --> 56:12.453
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

56:16.332 --> 56:20.628
Forget Hollywood screenplays.
Forget those distractions, huh?

56:22.088 --> 56:24.173
What, you think I haven't had offers?

56:26.675 --> 56:29.804
We got work to do. New avenues.

56:30.304 --> 56:34.183
Everything's gonna be all right
from here on in. Come on.

56:35.309 --> 56:38.813
Look, it's a beautiful day.
What could be bad?

56:41.065 --> 56:44.652
It's nice of you to pick me up
for the party, Junior.

56:45.569 --> 56:48.948
- At least somebody cares about me.
- These kids today.

56:49.156 --> 56:52.660
I suppose he thinks once he's
got me in a nursing home...

56:52.952 --> 56:57.665
...I'll die faster and then
he won't have to drive me anywhere.

56:58.290 --> 57:00.084
If his father was still alive...

57:00.334 --> 57:05.089
...you can bet he'd show more
decency and respect for his mother.

57:05.339 --> 57:08.384
Well, my brother John
was a man among men.

57:09.844 --> 57:11.220
He was a saint.

57:11.470 --> 57:15.182
Lots of things are different now
from Johnny's and my day.

57:15.349 --> 57:16.517
What do you mean?

57:16.725 --> 57:19.228
I'm not free to run my business
like I want.

57:19.478 --> 57:20.855
Aw, isn't that awful.

57:21.105 --> 57:22.898
Just this week, your son
stuck his hand in...

57:23.190 --> 57:25.317
...and made it 100 times
more difficult for me.

57:25.526 --> 57:27.611
Plus, he thumbs his nose at New York.

57:28.696 --> 57:32.199
What are you gonna do?
He's part of a whole generation.

57:33.367 --> 57:36.162
Do you remember the crazy hair?
And the dope?

57:36.370 --> 57:37.705
Now it's fags in the military.

57:37.872 --> 57:40.749
Stop it, Junior.
You're making me very upset!

57:41.041 --> 57:44.253
I don't like to, Livia,
but I'm <i>agita</i> all the time.

57:44.712 --> 57:48.215
And I'll tell you something else,
things are down all across the board.

57:48.549 --> 57:50.759
A lot of friends of ours
are complaining.

57:51.051 --> 57:54.513
We used to be recession-proof.
No more.

57:55.347 --> 57:58.267
You can't blame it all
on the Justice Department.

57:59.894 --> 58:01.645
Our friends say to me...

58:01.896 --> 58:06.567
..."Junior, why don't you
take a larger hand in things?"

58:09.236 --> 58:12.907
Something may have to be done, Livia,
about Tony.

58:13.866 --> 58:15.159
I don't know.

58:22.750 --> 58:24.543
There they are.
Hey, Ma, Uncle Jun.

58:24.752 --> 58:29.590
You're using mesquite.
That makes the sausage taste peculiar.

58:29.798 --> 58:33.302
- Hi, Grandma.
- Happy birthday, my big boy.

58:33.552 --> 58:34.929
Carmela, my mother's here.

58:35.179 --> 58:37.681
Everybody, let's eat.
